parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control, especially when driving at high speeds, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: the engine shuts off without warning
the vehicle is unable to restart
the vehicle experiences a loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Engine Idle Air Control System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty engine idle air control system can cause the engine to stall or cut off, leading to a loss of control, especially when downshifting or coming to a stop, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or cuts off when downshifting or coming to a stop
the vehicle experiences a loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A loose or detached grip can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries to the rider.
symptoms: The grip comes off while riding

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Saddle Bag Interference with Rear Reflector
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The saddle bags blocking the rear reflectors can reduce the motorcycle's visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Saddle bags obstruct the rear reflectors

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Rear Wheel Lock-up
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and rear wheel lock-up can cause loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Wheel Lock-up and Loss of Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The front wheel lock-up can cause loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
The failure of the rear brake light switch can cause the brake lights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of rear-end collisions.
symptoms: The brake lights do not illuminate when the brake pedal is pressed
the brake lights remain illuminated even when the brake pedal is not pressed
the brake lights flicker or dim
the brake light warning light on the dashboard is illuminated.
